column4: <content>Unfaithful Shepherd based on Coeck, Conversion of Paul (see Badt Festschrift); Also Bol drawings in Witt Coll. Painting attr. Corn. Massys (Witt photograph); Symbolism: Dead trees on left against the delicate fresh foliage on the right. Death and new life!</content>

<part_of.title>John X, 11: I am the good shepherd: the good shepherd giveth his life for the sheep. (cf. Js [Isaiah] 40, 11; Ezek 34, 12, 23 & 37, 24; Hebr. 13, 20; Pet. 2, 25 & 5,4) ...[sic] 15 As the Father knoweth me, even so know I the Father: and I lay down my life for the sheep. The expression is not horror- it is Christ's idealised head, not a peasant's.</part_of.title>
